
[1]aforehand

   AFO'REHAND, adv. [afore and hand.]

   1. In time previous; by previous provision; as, he is ready aforehand.

   She is come aforehand to anoint my body. Mark 14.

   2. a. Prepared; previously provided; as, to be aforehand in business.
   Hence in popular language, amply provided; well supplied with the means
   of living; having means beyond the requirements of necessity;
   moderately wealthy. The word is popularly changed into aforehanded,
   beforehanded, or rather forehanded; as, a forehanded farmer.
